==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Omniscient
<hw>Om*nis"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Omni-</ets>
+ L. <ets>sciens</ets>, -<ets>entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>scire</ets> to
know: cf. F. <ets>omniscient</ets>. See <er>Science</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having universal knowledge; knowing all things; infinitely knowing
or wise; <as>as, the <ex>omniscient</ex> God</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Om*nis"cient*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For what can scape the eye⟦br⟧
Of God all-seeing, or deceive his heart⟦br⟧
<qex>Omniscient</qex>?</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omniscious</ent>⟦br⟧
